One problem with salary prediction is that it's oddly distributed: there are many people who are paid standard salaries and a few that get tons o money. The distribution is fat-tailed on the right side, which is inconvenient for MSE minimization.

There are several techniques to combat this: using a different loss function, predicting log-target instead of raw target or even replacing targets with their percentiles among all salaries in the training set. We gonna use logarithm for now.

You can read more in the official description.

Preprocessing text data¶

Just like last week, applying NLP to a problem begins from tokenization: splitting raw text into sequences of tokens (words, punctuation, etc).

Your task is to lowercase and tokenize all texts under Title and FullDescription columns. Store the tokenized data as a space-separated string of tokens for performance reasons.

It's okay to use nltk tokenizers. Assertions were designed for WordPunctTokenizer, slight deviations are okay.

UNK_IX, PAD_IX = map(token_to_id.get, [UNK, PAD])
In [11]:
def as_matrix(sequences, max_len=27):
    """ Convert a list of tokens into a matrix with padding """
    if isinstance(sequences[0], str):
        sequences = list(map(str.split, sequences))
    
    matrix = np.full((len(sequences), max_len), np.int32(PAD_IX))
    for i,seq in enumerate(sequences):
        row_ix = [token_to_id.get(word, UNK_IX) for word in seq[:max_len]]
        matrix[i, :len(row_ix)] = row_ix
    
    return matrix

The deep learning part¶

Once we've learned to tokenize the data, let's design a machine learning experiment.

As before, we won't focus too much on validation, opting for a simple train-test split.

To be completely rigorous, we've comitted a small crime here: we used the whole data for tokenization and vocabulary building. A more strict way would be to do that part on training set only. You may want to do that and measure the magnitude of changes.

In [13]:
def train_test_val_split(data, batch_size):
  data_train, data_test = train_test_split(data, test_size=0.1, random_state=77)

  data_test, data_val = train_test_split(data_test, test_size=0.5, random_state=77)

  data_train = data_train[:(len(data_train) // batch_size) * batch_size]
  data_test = data_test[:(len(data_test) // batch_size) * batch_size]
  data_val = data_val[:(len(data_val) // batch_size) * batch_size]

  return data_train, data_test, data_val
In [26]:
def to_tensors(batch, device):
    batch_tensors = dict()
    for key, arr in batch.items():
        if key in ["FullDescription", "Title"]:
            batch_tensors[key] = torch.tensor(arr, device=device, dtype=torch.int64)
        else:
            batch_tensors[key] = torch.tensor(arr, device=device)
    return batch_tensors

def make_batch(data, max_len=27, word_dropout=0, device=torch.device('cpu')):
    """
    Creates a keras-friendly dict from the batch data.
    :param word_dropout: replaces token index with UNK_IX with this probability
    :returns: a dict with {'title' : int64[batch, title_max_len]
    """
    batch = {}
    batch["Title"] = as_matrix(data["Title"].values, max_len)
    batch["FullDescription"] = as_matrix(data["FullDescription"].values, max_len)
    batch['Categorical'] = categorical_vectorizer.transform(data[categorical_columns].apply(dict, axis=1))
    
    if word_dropout != 0:
        batch["FullDescription"] = apply_word_dropout(batch["FullDescription"], 1. - word_dropout)
    
    if TARGET_COLUMN in data.columns:
        batch[TARGET_COLUMN] = data[TARGET_COLUMN].values
    
    return to_tensors(batch, device)

def apply_word_dropout(matrix, keep_prop, replace_with=UNK_IX, pad_ix=PAD_IX,):
    dropout_mask = np.random.choice(2, np.shape(matrix), p=[keep_prop, 1 - keep_prop])
    dropout_mask &= matrix != pad_ix
    return np.choose(dropout_mask, [matrix, np.full_like(matrix, replace_with)])

Architecture¶

Our basic model consists of three branches:

  • Title encoder
  • Description encoder
  • Categorical features encoder

We will then feed all 3 branches into one common network that predicts salary.

This clearly doesn't fit into keras' Sequential interface. To build such a network, one will have to use PyTorch.

In [17]:
import torch
import torch.nn as nn
import torch.functional as F
In [ ]:
class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=8):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding(n_tokens, hid_size)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )
        #  YOUR CODE HERE

        
    def forward(self, batch):
        # YOUR CODE HERE
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])
        # print(title_features.shape, description_features.shape, categorical_features.shape)
        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)
        
        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

Training and evaluation¶

As usual, we gonna feed our monster with random minibatches of data.

As we train, we want to monitor not only loss function, which is computed in log-space, but also the actual error measured in dollars.

In [18]:
def iterate_minibatches(data, batch_size=256, shuffle=True, cycle=False, **kwargs):
    """ iterates minibatches of data in random order """
    while True:
        indices = np.arange(len(data))
        if shuffle:
            indices = np.random.permutation(indices)

        for start in range(0, len(indices), batch_size):
            batch = make_batch(data.iloc[indices[start : start + batch_size]], **kwargs)
            yield batch
        
        if not cycle: break

Model training¶

We can now fit our model the usual minibatch way. The interesting part is that we train on an infinite stream of minibatches, produced by iterate_minibatches function.

def print_metrics(model, in_data, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, h=None, name="", **kw):
    squared_error = abs_error = num_samples = 0.0
    model.eval()
    with torch.no_grad():
        for batch in iterate_minibatches(in_data, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=False, **kw):
            '''print('Print metrics batch Title shape ', batch['Title'].shape)
            print('Print metrics batch Description shape ', batch['FullDescription'].shape)'''
            if h is not None:
              batch_pred = model(batch, h)
            else:
              batch_pred = model(batch)
            loss = criterion(batch_pred, batch[TARGET_COLUMN])
            squared_error += torch.mean(torch.square(batch_pred - batch[TARGET_COLUMN]))
            abs_error += torch.mean(torch.abs(batch_pred - batch[TARGET_COLUMN]))
            num_samples += len(batch)
    mse = squared_error.detach().cpu().numpy() / num_samples
    mae = abs_error.detach().cpu().numpy() / num_samples

    print("%s results:" % (name or ""))
    print("Loss: %.5f" % loss.item())
    print("Mean square error: %.5f" % mse)
    print("Mean absolute error: %.5f" % mae)

    return mse, mae
In [34]:
def train(model, criterion, optimizer, has_reccurent = False):

  losses = []
  loss_iters = []
  metrics_iters = []
  train_mae = []
  train_mse = []
  test_mae = []
  test_mse = []

  cur_iter = 0

  for epoch in range(EPOCHS):
    print(f"epoch: {epoch}")
    if has_reccurent == True:
      h = model.init_hidden(BATCH_SIZE)
    for i, batch in tqdm.notebook.tqdm(enumerate(
            iterate_minibatches(
                    data_train, 
                    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, 
                    device=DEVICE)), 
                total=len(data_train) // BATCH_SIZE
        ):
        model.train()
        if has_reccurent == True:
          pred = model(batch, h)
        else:
          pred = model(batch)
        
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        loss = criterion(pred, batch[TARGET_COLUMN])
        loss_iters.append(cur_iter)

        losses.append(float(loss)/BATCH_SIZE)
        
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        if i % 100 == 99:
            if has_reccurent == True:
              val_h = model.init_hidden(BATCH_SIZE)
              mse, mae = print_metrics(model, data_train[:len(data_test)], name='train', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, h=val_h, device=DEVICE)
              train_mse.append(mse)
              train_mae.append(mae)
              mse, mae = print_metrics(model, data_test, name='test', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, h=val_h, device=DEVICE)
              test_mse.append(mse)
              test_mae.append(mae)
            else:
              mse, mae = print_metrics(model, data_train[:len(data_test)], name='train', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, device=DEVICE)
              train_mse.append(mse)
              train_mae.append(mae)
              mse, mae = print_metrics(model, data_test, name='test', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, device=DEVICE)
              test_mse.append(mse)
              test_mae.append(mae)
            metrics_iters.append(cur_iter)
        
        cur_iter += 1

  return losses, loss_iters, metrics_iters, train_mae, train_mse, test_mae, test_mse
In [23]:
def show_plots(losses, loss_iters, metrics_iters, train_mae, train_mse, test_mae, test_mse, val_mse, val_mae):
  plt.plot(loss_iters[:2000], losses[:2000])
  plt.title("Training Loss Curve (batch_size={}, lr={})".format(BATCH_SIZE, 1e-3))
  plt.xlabel("Iterations")
  plt.ylabel("Loss")
  plt.show()

  plt.title("Train, Test MSE (batch_size={}, lr={})".format(BATCH_SIZE, 1e-3))
  plt.plot(metrics_iters, train_mse, label="Train MSE")
  plt.plot(metrics_iters, test_mse, label="Test MSE")
  plt.xlabel("Iterations")
  plt.ylabel("MSE")
  plt.legend(loc='best')
  plt.show()

  plt.title("Train, Test MAE (batch_size={}, lr={})".format(BATCH_SIZE, 1e-3))
  plt.plot(metrics_iters, train_mae, label="Train MAE")
  plt.plot(metrics_iters, test_mae, label="Test MAE")
  plt.xlabel("Iterations")
  plt.ylabel("MAE")
  plt.legend(loc='best')
  plt.show()

  print("Final Train MSE: {}".format(train_mse[-1]))
  print("Final Train MAE: {}".format(train_mae[-1]))
  print("Final Test MSE: {}".format(test_mse[-1]))
  print("Final Test MAE: {}".format(test_mae[-1]))
  print("Val MSE: {}".format(val_mse))
  print("Val MAE: {}".format(val_mae))

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=8):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding(n_tokens, hid_size)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )
        
    def forward(self, batch):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)
        
        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=8):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding(n_tokens, hid_size)
        self.title_conv1 = nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2)
        self.title_conv2 = nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2)
        self.description_conv1 = nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2)
        self.description_conv2 = nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 6, hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )

def train_with_early_stopping(model, criterion, optimizer):
  losses = []
  loss_iters = []
  metrics_iters = []
  train_mae = []
  train_mse = []
  test_mae = []
  test_mse = []

  cur_iter = 0
  last_loss = 1000
  patience = 5 #  mse  5  ,    
  trigger_times = 0
  mse = 0

  for epoch in range(EPOCHS):
    print(f"epoch: {epoch}")
    for i, batch in tqdm.notebook.tqdm(enumerate(
            iterate_minibatches(
                    data_train, 
                    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, 
                    device=DEVICE)), 
                total=len(data_train) // BATCH_SIZE
        ):
        model.train()
        pred = model(batch)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        loss = criterion(pred, batch[TARGET_COLUMN])
        loss_iters.append(cur_iter)

        losses.append(float(loss)/BATCH_SIZE)
        
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        if i % 100 == 99:
            mse, mae = print_metrics(model, data_train[:len(data_test)], name='train', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, device=DEVICE)
            train_mse.append(mse)
            train_mae.append(mae)
            mse, mae = print_metrics(model, data_test, name='test', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, device=DEVICE)
            test_mse.append(mse)
            test_mae.append(mae)
            metrics_iters.append(cur_iter)
        
        if mse > last_loss:
            trigger_times += 1
            print('trigger times:', trigger_times)

            if trigger_times >= patience:
                raise Exception('Early stopping!')
        else:
            trigger_times = 0

        last_loss = mse

        cur_iter += 1

  return losses, loss_iters, metrics_iters, train_mae, train_mse, test_mae, test_mse

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=8):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding(n_tokens, hid_size)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )
        
    def forward(self, batch):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)
        
        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=8):
        super().__init__()
        self.title_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['Title'][0])
        self.description_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['FullDescription'][0])
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding(n_tokens, hid_size)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size*2, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size*2, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25)
        )
        self.title_pooling = nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size*2, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size*2, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25)
        )
        self.description_pooling = nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor_in = 34 
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(self.final_predictor_in, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )
        
    def forward(self, batch):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_pooling = self.title_pooling(title_features).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_pooling = self.description_pooling(description_features).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])
        features = torch.cat(
            [title_pooling, description_pooling, categorical_features], dim=1)
        self.final_predictor_in = len(features[1])
        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=8):
        super().__init__()
        self.title_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['Title'][0])
        self.description_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['FullDescription'][0])
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding(n_tokens, hid_size, padding_idx = 1)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size*2, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size*2, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25)
        )
        self.title_pooling = nn.AvgPool1d(hid_size, count_include_pad = False)
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size*2, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size*2, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25)
        )
        self.description_pooling = nn.AvgPool1d(hid_size, count_include_pad = False)
        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor_in = 34 
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(self.final_predictor_in, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )
        
    def forward(self, batch):
        # print('batch[Title]', batch['Title'])
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_pooling = self.title_pooling(title_features).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_pooling = self.description_pooling(description_features).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_pooling, description_pooling, categorical_features], dim=1)
        self.final_predictor_in = len(features[1])
        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=100):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding.from_pretrained(torch.FloatTensor(weights))
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.classifier = nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)

    def forward(self, batch):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)
        
        return self.classifier(self.final_predictor(features)).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=100):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding.from_pretrained(torch.FloatTensor(weights), freeze = False)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.classifier = nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        
    def forward(self, batch):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)
        
        return self.classifier(self.final_predictor(features)).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=256, n_layers=2):
        super().__init__()
        self.title_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['Title'][0])
        self.description_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['FullDescription'][0])

        self.hid_size = hid_size
        self.n_layers = n_layers

        self.embedder = nn.Embedding.from_pretrained(torch.FloatTensor(weights))

        self.title_encoder_LSTM = nn.LSTM(self.title_input_len, hid_size, n_layers, dropout=0.5, batch_first=True)

        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25)
        )

        self.description_encoder_LSTM = nn.LSTM(self.description_input_len, hid_size, n_layers, dropout=0.5, batch_first=True)

        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25) 
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )

    def init_hidden(self, batch_size):
        hidden = (torch.zeros(self.n_layers, batch_size, self.hid_size).cuda(),
                  torch.zeros(self.n_layers, batch_size, self.hid_size).cuda())

        return hidden
        
    def forward(self, batch, hidden):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_out, title_hidden = self.title_encoder_LSTM(title_embeddings, hidden)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_out[:, -1, :])

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_out, description_hidden = self.description_encoder_LSTM(description_embeddings, hidden)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_out[:, -1, :])

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)

        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=256, n_layers=2, bi_directional = True):
        super().__init__()
        self.title_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['Title'][0])
        self.description_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['FullDescription'][0])
        
        if bi_directional:
            self.dim = 2
        else:
            self.dim = 1

        self.hid_size = hid_size
        self.n_layers = n_layers

        self.embedder = nn.Embedding.from_pretrained(torch.FloatTensor(weights))

        self.title_encoder_LSTM = nn.LSTM(self.title_input_len, hid_size, n_layers, dropout=0.5, batch_first=True, bidirectional = True)

        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.Linear(self.dim * hid_size, hid_size)
        )

        self.description_encoder_LSTM = nn.LSTM(self.description_input_len, hid_size, n_layers, dropout=0.5, batch_first=True, bidirectional = True)

        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.Linear(self.dim * hid_size, hid_size)   
        )


        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )

        
    def forward(self, batch, hidden):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_out, title_hidden = self.title_encoder_LSTM(title_embeddings, hidden)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_out[:, -1, :])

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_out, description_hidden = self.description_encoder_LSTM(description_embeddings, hidden)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_out[:, -1, :])

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)

        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

    def init_hidden(self, batch_size):
        hidden = (torch.zeros(self.dim * self.n_layers, batch_size, self.hid_size).cuda(),
                    torch.zeros(self.dim * self.n_layers, batch_size, self.hid_size).cuda())

        return hidden

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=256, n_layers=2):
        super().__init__()
        self.title_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['Title'][0])
        self.description_input_len = len(make_batch(data_train[:BATCH_SIZE])['FullDescription'][0])
        self.weights_len = len(weights[0])

        self.hid_size = hid_size
        self.n_layers = n_layers

        self.embedder = nn.Embedding.from_pretrained(torch.FloatTensor(weights))

        self.title_encoder_CNN = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(self.weights_len, 2*hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size*2, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
        )

        self.title_encoder_LSTM = nn.LSTM(13, hid_size, n_layers, dropout=0.5, batch_first=True)

        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25) 
        )

        self.description_encoder_CNN = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(self.weights_len, 2*hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size*2, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
        )

        self.description_encoder_LSTM = nn.LSTM(13, hid_size, n_layers, dropout=0.5, batch_first=True)

        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25)    
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)
        )

        
    def forward(self, batch, hidden):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_convolution = self.title_encoder_CNN(title_embeddings)
        title_out, title_hidden = self.title_encoder_LSTM(title_convolution, hidden)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_out[:, -1, :])

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_convolution = self.description_encoder_CNN(description_embeddings)
        description_out, description_hidden = self.description_encoder_LSTM(description_convolution, hidden)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_out[:, -1, :])

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)

        return self.final_predictor(features).squeeze()

    def init_hidden(self, batch_size):
        hidden = (torch.zeros(self.n_layers, batch_size, self.hid_size).cuda(),
                  torch.zeros(self.n_layers, batch_size, self.hid_size).cuda())

        return hidden

class SalaryPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, n_tokens=len(tokens), n_cat_features=len(categorical_vectorizer.vocabulary_), hid_size=100):
        super().__init__()
        self.embedder = nn.Embedding.from_pretrained(torch.FloatTensor(weights), freeze = False)
        self.title_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )
        self.description_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=2),
            nn.MaxPool1d(2),
            nn.Conv1d(hid_size, hid_size, kernel_size=1),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.25),
            nn.AdaptiveMaxPool1d(output_size=1)
        )

        self.categorical_encoder = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(n_cat_features, hid_size * 4),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 4, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.final_predictor = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 3, hid_size * 2),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size * 2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(hid_size * 2, hid_size),
            nn.BatchNorm1d(hid_size),
            nn.ReLU()
        )
        self.classifier = nn.Linear(hid_size, 1)

    def forward(self, batch):
        title_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['Title']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        title_features = self.title_encoder(title_embeddings).squeeze()

        description_embeddings = self.embedder(batch['FullDescription']).permute(0, 2, 1)
        description_features = self.description_encoder(description_embeddings).squeeze()

        categorical_features = self.categorical_encoder(batch['Categorical'])

        features = torch.cat(
            [title_features, description_features, categorical_features], dim=1)
        
        return self.classifier(self.final_predictor(features)).squeeze()
